reviews.review_text:
Her Angels in Flame... My God.  What a depressing show.

I remember this one.  During "Slipknot" Bobby actually walked over to Jerry and tried to show him the chord progression so he could keep playing.  That was the end of my "Dead career".

The fact that they went out on a Summer tour with Jer in such bad shape was shameful to say the least.

disagree (This is a great show but this Source plays a half step slow and should be not listened to.  If it were pitch corrected it wouldn't be a bad aud source)

I hear weird Acid Trip stuff about 95 like that last review all the time. Yeah I went to a few 95 shows and I was shocked the first time I saw Jerry in his condition. But eventually you have to out grow that initial knee jerk reaction to really dig in and understand the music and what's going on at that time. If you do, you would realize that this show is actually very good. And that the Omni run overall stands out. Jerry struggled and fought during 95 but when he was feeling good he and the band could hook up as good as ever, and this show has that.  the opening Jack straw kicks ass and there's a bunch of highlights throughout. This just might not be the best source of the soundboard by Charlie Miller mastering and it's the s***. Don't pass up the sunny V show and don't believe people that stayed silly stuff like 95 was just a joke and you shouldn't even listen to it. I get people got tired of touring then and Jerry not being a good shape may have one of them to quit touring but it's your fault for going to a billion Dead shows and wasting your time like that.
